FBIS3-50711 "drlat004_c_94016" FBIS-LAT-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 MEXICO Chiapas Crisis Salinas Asks Ombudsman To Ensure Human Rights PA0601015994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0041 GMT 6 Jan 94 PA0601015994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Elizabeth Diaz Otero from the "Vector 21" newscast] [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has reaffirmed that respect for the civilian population's human rights, along with gauarantees that allow media representatives to carry out their duties, is of foremost importance in the search for a solution to the conflict in Chiapas. The president ordered the people responsible for organizations involved in operations in the Chiapas highlands to ensure this. The Mexican president on 5 January asked Jorge Madrazo Cuellar, president of the National Human Rights Commission, to visit Chiapas to correct any situation that might harm civil rights. The Mexican ombudsman headed for San Cristobal de las Casas on the afternoon of 5 January.
